    },
    {
      "id": "z25VicN3uCird5MTniaF1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1170.112373921342,
      "y": 38070.06544892791,
      "width": 473,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWm",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 319734955,
      "version": 54,
      "versionNonce": 2062870123,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772383891623,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is DNS and what is the process of DNS?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What is DNS and what is the process of DNS?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "1MfrvTybIaEkLBoFolk7i",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1237.221748921342,
      "y": 38106.01857392791,
      "width": 935,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWo",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1022844107,
      "version": 1352,
      "versionNonce": 477910091,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772384607068,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What happens is when our system is asked to hit google.com, first of all it checks\nwithin itself that Do I know the Ip of xyz.com, If it doesn't know, It will reach\nout to its router or Gateway(whatever mobile hotspot or what DHCP Gateway) to check\nwhether its Gateway knows the Ip of xyz.com, Assume Router also don't know, \nObviously Router is also connected with Many routers along the way like Local ISP\nZone or Regional ISP and so on, lets say noone knows, due to its not google.com\nit is something which is not hit so frequently, In that case our final query(We are\nskipping all the systems whihc are in between) will hit to a server called as\nDNS(Domain Name Server). This DNS don't store any IP address, What it does is that\nin the backend there are few other server that it will connect with or communicate\nwith, this other system(server) is called as Root Name server(RNS). Now RNS will also\nnot store IP address, If we see our domain name clearly, Domain name goes like lets\nsay google.com so RNS will break that into parts and it will tell us that I dont know\ngoogle.com but I know where all the addresses of all the .com are.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What happens is when our system is asked to hit google.com, first of all it checks\nwithin itself that Do I know the Ip of xyz.com, If it doesn't know, It will reach\nout to its router or Gateway(whatever mobile hotspot or what DHCP Gateway) to check\nwhether its Gateway knows the Ip of xyz.com, Assume Router also don't know, \nObviously Router is also connected with Many routers along the way like Local ISP\nZone or Regional ISP and so on, lets say noone knows, due to its not google.com\nit is something which is not hit so frequently, In that case our final query(We are\nskipping all the systems whihc are in between) will hit to a server called as\nDNS(Domain Name Server). This DNS don't store any IP address, What it does is that\nin the backend there are few other server that it will connect with or communicate\nwith, this other system(server) is called as Root Name server(RNS). Now RNS will also\nnot store IP address, If we see our domain name clearly, Domain name goes like lets\nsay google.com so RNS will break that into parts and it will tell us that I dont know\ngoogle.com but I know where all the addresses of all the .com are.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fkvC1KkfwngFWqAQU8_9d",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1239.374092671342,
      "y": 38489.89748017791,
      "width": 275,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWp",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1594102827,
      "version": 36,
      "versionNonce": 400210603,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772384831345,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why is it done like this?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why is it done like this?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "w1m2rYURH66TYVr5DkOqF",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1277.241280171342,
      "y": 38524.51857392791,
      "width": 990,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWs",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1746148235,
      "version": 584,
      "versionNonce": 2074343947,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772385080102,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "the reason behind is , there are so many websites in the world, there are .com, .in, .edu,\n.eu, .gov and so on, there are so many types of websites. If all are there on a same \nsystem, To find a specific IP address it will take lot of time, So just to manage that\n.com is kept at one place, .edu is kept at another place, .org is kept at another place\nIf we ask for .com, it will go to Root Name Server(RNS), RNS will tell me that all the\n.coms are here you can try and search over here for google.com.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "the reason behind is , there are so many websites in the world, there are .com, .in, .edu,\n.eu, .gov and so on, there are so many types of websites. If all are there on a same \nsystem, To find a specific IP address it will take lot of time, So just to manage that\n.com is kept at one place, .edu is kept at another place, .org is kept at another place\nIf we ask for .com, it will go to Root Name Server(RNS), RNS will tell me that all the\n.coms are here you can try and search over here for google.com.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "bEjHkPL8hiBCOjoXgjEKZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1226.608467671342,
      "y": 38733.74904267791,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWu",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 201898725,
      "version": 388,
      "versionNonce": 1383467755,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772386108986,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now DNS know the address of .coms, then DNS will hit the query or a search for .com to a diff\nkind of server, this server over here it is called as my TLD(Top Level Domain) server. TLD still\nwill not give us final IP address, TLD will give us the address(IP) of the corresponding System(ANS) \nto go and get the Ip of google.com",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now DNS know the address of .coms, then DNS will hit the query or a search for .com to a diff\nkind of server, this server over here it is called as my TLD(Top Level Domain) server. TLD still\nwill not give us final IP address, TLD will give us the address(IP) of the corresponding System(ANS) \nto go and get the Ip of google.com",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "sdwEAwN3c2isUsent9yrS",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1225.167061421342,
      "y": 38881.63576142791,
      "width": 913,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWw",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 650477477,
      "version": 128,
      "versionNonce": 163294795,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772385761872,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q Why TLD server is returning us the Address of a system that has IP of google.com?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q Why TLD server is returning us the Address of a system that has IP of google.com?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "1P_BhgntxClXDiL8qBMtA",
      "type": "text",
