      "updated": 1772559319661,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "www.google.com:443|geo_location\n    the nearest Root Server which is nearest to this geo location, DNS will be hitting to that\nRNS. these 13-15 RNS are spread across the world.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "www.google.com:443|geo_location\n    the nearest Root Server which is nearest to this geo location, DNS will be hitting to that\nRNS. these 13-15 RNS are spread across the world.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "nHm4owziSLs4KRjB24k9D",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1063.801827046342,
      "y": 42584.04005830291,
      "width": 1133,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bYY",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1597737706,
      "version": 295,
      "versionNonce": 701059062,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772559527380,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q -> I am trying to hit a server, Lets say who is out there in US, I am hitting a website something\nsomething.us, there are no servers in India, How do I think I communicate or I get the data from there?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q -> I am trying to hit a server, Lets say who is out there in US, I am hitting a website something\nsomething.us, there are no servers in India, How do I think I communicate or I get the data from there?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "AuZzGfplgKuw17Dgd_YkE",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1092.446358296342,
      "y": 42651.47755830291,
      "width": 1155,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bYc",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2112389174,
      "version": 1157,
      "versionNonce": 105730922,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772560928179,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "With the help of Optical Fibres -> Optical fibres are calles as deap see cables. These deep sea cables\nor the Optical fibres are first of all satellite are used. But not that much, Our 95 to 97% of the data\ntransmission is happening via deep sea cables.\nAmazon data centre is in Mumbai, the reason behind having data somewhere in Mumbai is because in India,\nthe major connections of our deep sea cables are going our either from Mumbai or from Chennai, So we \nwill see these are the locations most preferred for data center because inke cloud me or anyone deploying\nthere sever, and that server want to communicalte outside this gives us a easy connection point over\nhere. So they can directly connect with these Optic cables. So that is why all the data centers\nmajor data centers that we see whether it is of Reliance or Amazon or Meta or anything they are out \nthere in Mumbai. Some of them are in Chennai also but major one are in Mumbai only.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "With the help of Optical Fibres -> Optical fibres are calles as deap see cables. These deep sea cables\nor the Optical fibres are first of all satellite are used. But not that much, Our 95 to 97% of the data\ntransmission is happening via deep sea cables.\nAmazon data centre is in Mumbai, the reason behind having data somewhere in Mumbai is because in India,\nthe major connections of our deep sea cables are going our either from Mumbai or from Chennai, So we \nwill see these are the locations most preferred for data center because inke cloud me or anyone deploying\nthere sever, and that server want to communicalte outside this gives us a easy connection point over\nhere. So they can directly connect with these Optic cables. So that is why all the data centers\nmajor data centers that we see whether it is of Reliance or Amazon or Meta or anything they are out \nthere in Mumbai. Some of them are in Chennai also but major one are in Mumbai only.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "1CBUZD0XN3Zo4j9n3gdhk",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1036.090889546342,
      "y": 42986.16505830291,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bYe",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 929076214,
      "version": 913,
      "versionNonce": 131296054,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772561476570,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "There are Routers, Regional, Zonal, National there are different level of ISPs and there are diff systems\nwhen we talk of in a Network, So from My router to server there are diff systems\nNOw it is not like that problem is in start\nWe know problem is not in our system for sure, I have checked everything in my system, I have checked the\nfirewalls, caches, Gateways, I am able to hit my router also but beyond my Router I am not able to hit and\nI don't know what is happening beyond router that is not in my control, So how to check where the issue is\ncomming because issue is not necessarily in start or end any part can broke How will I check this. So this\npart everything is called as Hop. So going from one system to another system is called as a hop or a jump\nSo on which hop my issue is coming ?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "There are Routers, Regional, Zonal, National there are different level of ISPs and there are diff systems\nwhen we talk of in a Network, So from My router to server there are diff systems\nNOw it is not like that problem is in start\nWe know problem is not in our system for sure, I have checked everything in my system, I have checked the\nfirewalls, caches, Gateways, I am able to hit my router also but beyond my Router I am not able to hit and\nI don't know what is happening beyond router that is not in my control, So how to check where the issue is\ncomming because issue is not necessarily in start or end any part can broke How will I check this. So this\npart everything is called as Hop. So going from one system to another system is called as a hop or a jump\nSo on which hop my issue is coming ?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
