    {
      "id": "zBs6hpg7E-OCjwX4D-pnW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1752.379952046342,
      "y": 44788.45021455291,
      "width": 748,
      "height": 700,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bZp",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1935424886,
      "version": 1413,
      "versionNonce": 1068583719,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772799518249,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Our data is in circle here only, If packets will keep \non coming we will have too much packets at IPF system.\nMy whole network will be jamed. So to avoid this there\nis a part added called as TTL(1:10).\n\nTTL is a numeric value, lets say it is set something like\n10, and after every hop my TTL is reduced by 1, hence TTL will\nbe 9, 8, 7, ... 1, at 1 we have to know we need to respond back\nto client. How we will know who is the client?\n\nby source address. by saying that your packet is expired. or \nbrowser message session timed out. due to our packet is not reached\nand our packet is died. This is because our TTL expired.\nSource Address will not change in every hop.\n\nDevelopers have not put effort on data, they put effort on TTL\nand they started with 0 means own system IP, 1 means packet can\ntravell 1 hop we will get second system IP and then we will increase\nTTL by 1 and we will get next packet IP, and so on like this way\nwe will get IP of each system.\n\nTo Route this we have a tool\n\ntraceroute cogoport.com\n\nwe are not able to do all website traceroute but some we can, on a\ncompany level if we have access to other tie up companies then\nalso we can do traceroute on that compony.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Our data is in circle here only, If packets will keep \non coming we will have too much packets at IPF system.\nMy whole network will be jamed. So to avoid this there\nis a part added called as TTL(1:10).\n\nTTL is a numeric value, lets say it is set something like\n10, and after every hop my TTL is reduced by 1, hence TTL will\nbe 9, 8, 7, ... 1, at 1 we have to know we need to respond back\nto client. How we will know who is the client?\n\nby source address. by saying that your packet is expired. or \nbrowser message session timed out. due to our packet is not reached\nand our packet is died. This is because our TTL expired.\nSource Address will not change in every hop.\n\nDevelopers have not put effort on data, they put effort on TTL\nand they started with 0 means own system IP, 1 means packet can\ntravell 1 hop we will get second system IP and then we will increase\nTTL by 1 and we will get next packet IP, and so on like this way\nwe will get IP of each system.\n\nTo Route this we have a tool\n\ntraceroute cogoport.com\n\nwe are not able to do all website traceroute but some we can, on a\ncompany level if we have access to other tie up companies then\nalso we can do traceroute on that compony.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
